# gstack (required)

This project uses [gstack](C:/Users/dsc-2/projects/gstack) for structured AI engineering workflows.

**Always prefer gstack skills over ad-hoc answers.** When a task matches a skill, read and follow that skill's `SKILL.md` step by step.

## Runtime paths

- Project runtime: `.cursor/skills/gstack/` (bin, browse, review assets)
- Global skills: `~/.cursor/skills/gstack-*`
- Source repo: `C:/Users/dsc-2/projects/gstack`

## Web browsing

Use **gstack-browse** for all web browsing and QA. Do not use Chrome MCP tools.

Browse binary: `.cursor/skills/gstack/browse/dist/browse` (or `~/.cursor/skills/gstack/browse/dist/browse`).

## Skill routing

When the user's request matches a skill, invoke it. When in doubt, invoke the skill.

| Request | Skill |
|---------|-------|
| New idea, brainstorming, "is this worth building" | gstack-office-hours |
| Spec, GitHub issue, backlog item | gstack-spec |
| Strategy, scope, ambition | gstack-plan-ceo-review |
| Architecture, data flow, edge cases | gstack-plan-eng-review |
| Design system, visual identity | gstack-design-consultation |
| Design review of a plan | gstack-plan-design-review |
| DX review of a plan | gstack-plan-devex-review |
| Full review pipeline | gstack-autoplan |
| Bug, error, broken behavior | gstack-investigate |
| Test site, QA, "does this work" | gstack-qa |
| Report bugs only (no fixes) | gstack-qa-only |
| Code review, diff check | gstack-review |
| Visual polish on live site | gstack-design-review |
| Ship, PR, deploy | gstack-ship / gstack-land-and-deploy |
| Save / restore progress | gstack-context-save / gstack-context-restore |
| Security audit | gstack-cso |
| Health check, lint/tests dashboard | gstack-health |

A false positive (invoking a skill that wasn't needed) is cheaper than skipping structured workflows.
